<guide id="419" locale="en">
   <title subject="Bottom Bezel Bracket" type="installation">Installing iPod Nano 2nd Generation Bottom Bezel Bracket</title>
   <summary>This is a summary. It is less than 255 characters.</summary>
   <image guid="TFCKijfJ5fo2IADd" id="1801">http://nwelch.cominor.com/igi/TFCKijfJ5fo2IADd</image>
   <author id="1">iRobot</author>
   <time_required>10 minutes</time_required>
   <difficulty>Difficult</difficulty>
   <categories>
      <category>iPod Nano 2nd Generation</category>
   </categories>
   <introduction><p>The metal bracket within your iPod.</p></introduction>
   <tools>
      <tool thumbnail="http://cart-products.ifixit.net/cart-products/GtpNGCPhUURCXnXL.mini.jpg" url="http://nwelch.cominor.com/Tools/Metal-Spudger/IF145-012">Metal Spudger</tool>
      <tool thumbnail="http://cart-products.ifixit.net/cart-products/GGXkxBRrmZg6iRdE.mini.jpg" url="http://nwelch.cominor.com/Tools/Phillips-00-Screwdriver/IF145-006">Phillips #00 Screwdriver</tool>
      <tool url="http://nwelch.cominor.com/Item/Plastic_Opening_Tools">Plastic Opening Tools</tool>
   </tools>
   <parts>
      <part thumbnail="http://cart-products.ifixit.net/cart-products/CPiMKmSYDDea2nu1.mini.jpg" url="http://nwelch.cominor.com/iPod-Parts/iPod-Nano-Gen-2-Bottom-Bezel-Bracket/IF199-006">iPod Nano Gen 2 Bottom Bezel Bracket</part>
   </parts>
   <flags />
   <documents>
      <document id="138" url="http://cominor-documents.s3.amazonaws.com/UxujoG1XDgJ5qnRq.pdf">About-Stacks.pdf</document>
   </documents>
   <prerequisites>
      <prerequisite id="418" locale="en">Installing iPod Nano 2nd Generation Bottom Bezel</prerequisite>
   </prerequisites>
   <steps>
      <step number="1" title="">
         <lines>
            <line bullet="icon_note" level="0">Before opening your iPod, ensure that the hold switch is in the locked position.</line>
         </lines>
         <images>
            <image guid="NsEmgggSmqUmqyhX" id="1799" orderby="1">http://nwelch.cominor.com/igi/NsEmgggSmqUmqyhX</image>
         </images>
      </step>
      <step number="2" title="">
         <lines>
            <line bullet="icon_caution" level="0">When removing the the bottom bezel, be sure not to bend the plastic surrounding the dock connector.</line>
            <line bullet="black" level="0">Carefully insert an iPod opening tool in the seam between the metal casing and white plastic bezel</line>
            <line bullet="black" level="0">Lift the bottom bezel off the iPod. It's glued on using a mild adhesive, so some force may be required.</line>
         </lines>
         <images>
            <image guid="KmjiobyZTwMW2ZPM" id="1800" orderby="1">http://nwelch.cominor.com/igi/KmjiobyZTwMW2ZPM</image>
         </images>
      </step>
      <step number="3" title="">
         <lines>
            <line bullet="black" level="0">Remove the following two screws:</line>
            <line bullet="red" level="1">One #00 Phillips screw with a large head near the headphone jack.</line>
            <line bullet="orange" level="1">One #00 Phillips screw with a smaller head near the side of the iPod. This screw strips easily, so be sure to press down firmly on the screwdriver.</line>
         </lines>
         <images>
            <image guid="TFCKijfJ5fo2IADd" id="1801" orderby="1">http://nwelch.cominor.com/igi/TFCKijfJ5fo2IADd</image>
         </images>
      </step>
      <step number="4" title="">
         <lines>
            <line bullet="black" level="0">Use a metal spudger to carefully pry the headphone jack out of the casing. DO NOT remove the headphone jack from the iPod entirely, as it is connected via a fragile ribbon connector to the click wheel.</line>
         </lines>
         <images>
            <image guid="nVHmgObvCQ4JgWAp" id="1802" orderby="1">http://nwelch.cominor.com/igi/nVHmgObvCQ4JgWAp</image>
         </images>
      </step>
      <step number="5" title="">
         <lines>
            <line bullet="black" level="0">Slide the headphone jack out until the white plastic housing is no longer held in place by the metal casing.</line>
         </lines>
         <images>
            <image guid="X1m2sdcc2FLBg4R3" id="1803" orderby="1">http://nwelch.cominor.com/igi/X1m2sdcc2FLBg4R3</image>
         </images>
      </step>
      <step number="6" title="">
         <lines>
            <line bullet="black" level="0">Remove the newly-revealed Phillips #00 screw from beneath the headphone jack.</line>
         </lines>
         <images>
            <image guid="nOSSG6Nsi3qweRB1" id="1804" orderby="1">http://nwelch.cominor.com/igi/nOSSG6Nsi3qweRB1</image>
         </images>
      </step>
      <step number="7" title="">
         <lines>
            <line bullet="black" level="0">Lift the bottom bezel bracket out of the iPod.</line>
         </lines>
         <images>
            <image guid="SjVEOuRyNifK2QdQ" id="1805" orderby="1">http://nwelch.cominor.com/igi/SjVEOuRyNifK2QdQ</image>
         </images>
      </step>
   </steps>
   <conclusion><p>To reassemble your device, follow these instructions in reverse order.</p></conclusion>
</guide>

